#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:490
msgid "TextResponse objects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:494
msgid ""
":class:`TextResponse` objects adds encoding capabilities to the base :class:"
"`Response` class, which is meant to be used only for binary data, such as "
"images, sounds or any media file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:498
msgid ""
":class:`TextResponse` objects support a new constructor argument, in "
"addition to the base :class:`Response` objects. The remaining functionality "
"is the same as for the :class:`Response` class and is not documented here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:502
msgid ""
"is a string which contains the encoding to use for this response. If you "
"create a :class:`TextResponse` object with a unicode body, it will be "
"encoded using this encoding (remember the body attribute is always a "
"string). If ``encoding`` is ``None`` (default value), the encoding will be "
"looked up in the response headers and body instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/request-response.rst:509
msgid ""
